<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-10T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-10T11:00:00-05:00" n="307" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d307">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/6428: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Reed</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-10T17:00:00+01:00">September 10, 1937—5
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 6:16 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>407. My 404, September 8, 1 p.m. A high official of the Foreign Office
                            told me today that Italy has no intention of replying to the second
                            Soviet note and that consideration might eventually have to be given to
                            severance of diplomatic relations with that country.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Reed</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>